---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About The Modern Library">
  <header>
    <div class="container mx-auto flex justify-between items-center">
      <a href="/" class="text-xl font-bold font-poppins tracking-wider">The Modern Library</a>
      <nav class="hidden md:flex items-center space-x-8">
        <a href="/books" class="nav-link">Catalogue</a>
        <a href="/about" class="nav-link">About</a>
        <a href="#" class="nav-link">Submissions</a>
      </nav>
      <a href="/books" class="hidden md:block cta-button">Browse</a>
      <button class="md:hidden text-2xl">
        <!-- Mobile Menu Icon -->
        <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
          <line x1="3" y1="12" x2="21" y2="12"></line>
          <line x1="3" y1="6" x2="21" y2="6"></line>
          <line x1="3" y1="18" x2="21" y2="18"></line>
        </svg>
      </button>
    </div>
  </header>
  <main class="container mx-auto px-6 py-16 md:py-24">
    <section class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-24">
      <div class="text-pane">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl !leading-tight">About The Modern Library</h1>
        <p class="mt-6 text-lg md:text-xl max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          The Modern Library is a project dedicated to bringing classic literature to contemporary readers.
          We utilize advanced Large Language Models (LLMs) to modernize the language and context of timeless stories,
          making them accessible and engaging for a new generation, while meticulously preserving the original's essence and artistic integrity.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg md:text-xl max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          Our process emphasizes transparency, providing detailed insights into the LLM prompts and metadata used for each modernization.
          We also support multiple versions of each book, allowing readers to explore different interpretations and evolutions of the modernized texts.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg md:text-xl max-w-2xl mx-auto">
          All content on this site is dynamically generated from a source GitHub repository at build time,
          ensuring that our collection is always up-to-date and reflective of the latest modernizations.
          We believe in the power of technology to bridge the gap between classic literature and modern audiences,
          fostering a deeper appreciation for the enduring narratives that have shaped our world.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <footer>
    <div class="container mx-auto text-center text-sm">
      <p>&copy; 2025 The Modern Library. All Rights Reserved.</p>
      <p class="mt-2 font-poppins text-xs opacity-70">
        <a href="#" class="hover:text-[var(--accent-gold)]">Privacy Policy</a> &middot;         <a href="#" class="hover:text-[var(--accent-gold)]">Terms of Service</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>